name: libcacard
description:
This library provides emulation of smart cards to a virtual card reader running in a guest virtual machine.

It implements DoD CAC standard with separate pki containers (compatible with coolkey and OpenSC), using certificates read from NSS.

license_location_justification: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard/blob/master/COPYING
floss_license_justification: The GPL-2.0-or-later license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The GPL-2.0-or-later license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard/blob/master/README.md
repo_interim_justification: this is happening throughout the pull requests. For example https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard/merge_requests/4
repo_distributed_justification: git
release_notes_vulns_justification: no publicly known vulnerabilities so far
report_responses_justification:
According to the last year list of issues, this happens
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard/issues?scope=all&utf8=%E2%9C%93&state=all
vulnerability_report_private_justificati:
Both private issues and emails are provided
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: no vulnerabilities reported in last 6 months
warnings_justification: Using AX_COMPILER_FLAGS() which default to error
warnings_strict_justification: Using AX_COMPILER_FLAGS() which default to error, csbuild, clang separate CI target
crypto_published_justification: The CAC specifies only use of RSA keys, which are (indirectly through NSS) used here
crypto_keylength_justification: This library does not create any default mechanisms where the default would be enforced.
crypto_random_justification: no cryptographic keys nor nonces are generated in libcacard
delivery_mitm_justification:
releases are published through HTTPS with GPG signatures:
https://www.spice-space.org/download/libcacard/
static_analysis_justification:
gitlab CI targets for asan address sanitizer, clang and csbuild:
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard/blob/master/.gitlab-ci.yml
coverity scans are scheduled on downstream packages in RHEL.
static_analysis_often_justification: the targets are run as part of CI on every commit/merge request
dynamic_analysis_justification: oss-fuzz runs simple fuzzer in fuzz/ directory
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification:
Address sanitizer is run as part of CI
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard/blob/master/.gitlab-ci.yml
crypto_weaknesses_justification: The only hash that is used is SHA2
discussion_justification:
Gitlab issues and merge requests.
Spice-devel mailing list: https://lists.freedesktop.org/mailman/listinfo/spice-devel
